
00:00:10,021 --> 00:00:11,956
(TV playing, man speaking
indistinctly)

00:00:17,157 --> 00:00:19,014
(motorcycle revs in distance,
phone line rings)

00:00:19,014 --> 00:00:21,082
WOMAN: <i>911 operator.</i>
<i>What's your emergency?</i>

00:00:21,082 --> 00:00:22,984
(siren wails)
MAN:
<i>I'm at the Sky View Motel.</i>

00:00:22,984 --> 00:00:25,687
<i>I was making a delivery.</i>
<i>You have to send someone.</i>

00:00:25,687 --> 00:00:27,689
<i>I think they're dead.</i>
<i>I don't know for sure, but...</i>
<i>Slow down, sir.</i>

00:00:27,689 --> 00:00:28,757
<i>You need to tell me</i>
<i>what happened.</i>

00:00:28,757 --> 00:00:30,625
<i>Are there people injured?</i>

00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:31,927
MAN: <i>There's blood.</i>
<i>There's blood everywhere.</i>

00:00:31,927 --> 00:00:34,029
(siren chirps)

00:00:34,029 --> 00:00:35,997
(sighs wearily)
Well, it's a messy one.

00:00:35,997 --> 00:00:37,520
If you don't believe me,
ask the pizza

00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:39,656
delivery guy there.
STOKES:
Yeah, is he the one

00:00:39,656 --> 00:00:41,658
who called it in?
Yeah, he was
delivering pizzas

00:00:41,658 --> 00:00:44,060
to, uh, one of
the rooms nearby.

00:00:44,060 --> 00:00:46,729
The door to 114 was ajar,
so he looked in.

00:00:46,729 --> 00:00:49,032
What do we have?
Two victims.

00:00:49,032 --> 00:00:51,467
Mr. and Mrs. Smith.
Oh, that's original.

00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:52,735
Anybody know
who they really are?

00:00:52,735 --> 00:00:53,811
No.

00:00:53,811 --> 00:00:55,713
And I don't know what
they did to deserve this.

00:01:10,762 --> 00:01:14,666
PHILLIPS:
...63... 64... 65...

00:01:14,666 --> 00:01:17,101
66, 67...

00:01:17,101 --> 00:01:21,105
68... 69... 70...

00:01:21,105 --> 00:01:22,807
71, 72...
STOKES:
Talk to me, David.

00:01:22,807 --> 00:01:26,644
I'm trying to determine
the number of stab wounds.

00:01:26,644 --> 00:01:28,980
But, frankly, there are
just too many to count.

00:01:31,015 --> 00:01:32,517
FINLAY:
This is disturbing.

00:01:35,620 --> 00:01:37,622
STOKES:
Hey, wait a minute.

00:01:37,622 --> 00:01:40,024
You know something?
I've been here.

00:01:40,024 --> 00:01:43,127
Yeah, we had that OD out
on the street a while back.
Yeah, yeah,

00:01:43,127 --> 00:01:45,697
in the motel, but I mean,
in this room--this exact one.

00:01:45,697 --> 00:01:46,998
I-I've been here.

00:01:46,998 --> 00:01:49,534
Room 114.

00:01:49,534 --> 00:01:51,769
I remember the view of the neon
from that window.

00:01:51,769 --> 00:01:54,038
This is it.
You're right.

00:01:54,038 --> 00:01:56,641
We have been here before.
Yeah, it was

00:01:56,641 --> 00:01:59,043
a dismemberment murder;
victim was in his 20s.

00:01:59,043 --> 00:02:01,479
It was about, uh,
two months ago.
No, I think it was more recent.

00:02:01,479 --> 00:02:04,382
It was another couple,
but the woman was bludgeoned...

00:02:04,382 --> 00:02:05,683
in her sleep.

00:02:05,683 --> 00:02:07,585
I am pretty sure
it was the dismemberment.

00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:09,020
I'm sorry,
but-but you're both right.

00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:10,788
I've been here twice before,

00:02:10,788 --> 00:02:13,825
once for the dismemberment
and again for the couple.

00:02:13,825 --> 00:02:15,860
And now this.

00:02:15,860 --> 00:02:19,063
Anybody else getting a really
bad feeling about this place?

00:02:19,063 --> 00:02:22,934
Yeah... yeah, this the world's
most unlucky motel room.

00:02:29,841 --> 00:02:32,677
