00:02:32,677 --> 00:02:35,780
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:38,950
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,418
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:02:40,418 --> 00:02:42,687
♪ I really wanna know ♪

00:02:42,687 --> 00:02:45,156
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:02:45,156 --> 00:02:46,924
♪ Oh-oh-oh ♪
♪ <i>Who...</i> ♪

00:02:46,924 --> 00:02:50,628
♪ Come on, tell me who are you,
you, you ♪

00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:53,631
♪ Are you! ♪

00:03:00,638 --> 00:03:02,573
(indistinct radio communication,
siren wailing in distance)

00:03:14,452 --> 00:03:16,854
All right,
that's three murder scenes

00:03:16,854 --> 00:03:18,690
all in the same spot.

00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:20,558
They got to be related,
don't you think?

00:03:20,558 --> 00:03:23,394
Maybe there's a connection
between the victims

00:03:23,394 --> 00:03:26,064
or the killer has
a weird fixation of some kind.

00:03:26,064 --> 00:03:29,767
I don't think I'm ready to talk
about past crimes yet.

00:03:29,767 --> 00:03:31,869
Have to focus on
this one first.

00:03:31,869 --> 00:03:33,438
Yeah, I hear you.

00:03:33,438 --> 00:03:35,139
I'll take the bathroom.

00:04:01,799 --> 00:04:05,036
(man yelling, blade slicing)

00:04:24,122 --> 00:04:25,590
(woman screams)

00:04:27,525 --> 00:04:29,927
(woman screaming)

00:04:34,465 --> 00:04:36,768
BRASS: So, how long have
you been manager here?

00:04:36,768 --> 00:04:39,036
Uh, since about the time
I learned to walk.

00:04:39,036 --> 00:04:41,372
My parents built this place,
so... I grew up here.

00:04:41,372 --> 00:04:42,373
Oh!
Yeah.

00:04:42,373 --> 00:04:43,708
All mine now.

00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:45,510
Do you have any idea
who might've done this?

00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:48,546
Isn't that your business
to figure that out?

00:04:48,546 --> 00:04:49,847
I mean, I know we're
not the Bellagio, but...

00:04:49,847 --> 00:04:52,583
if I have to drop
the rates any lower,

00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,051
I might as well just
board the place up.

00:04:54,051 --> 00:04:57,588
Yeah. So, you got about, what,
uh, 20 rooms here?

00:04:57,588 --> 00:04:59,857
Tell me about the people
who stay in them.

00:04:59,857 --> 00:05:01,659
It's like the sign says.
I mean, by the night,

00:05:01,659 --> 00:05:03,628
by the week and by the month.

00:05:03,628 --> 00:05:04,929
I'm gonna need a list of names.

00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:06,731
Well, that could be a problem.

00:05:06,731 --> 00:05:07,899
Not that I wouldn't
give it, it's just...

00:05:07,899 --> 00:05:08,833
I don't have it.

00:05:09,801 --> 00:05:11,402
Come on, man.

00:05:11,402 --> 00:05:13,638
The place is 39 bucks a night.

00:05:13,638 --> 00:05:15,072
If people have cash,

00:05:15,072 --> 00:05:16,874
what do I care
about their names?

00:05:16,874 --> 00:05:20,411
Look, none of 'em are
killers, though-- trust me.

00:05:20,411 --> 00:05:22,847
How do you know that?

00:05:22,847 --> 00:05:25,683
Well, there's no one here
that interesting.

00:05:45,670 --> 00:05:46,904
(liquid sloshing)

00:06:07,058 --> 00:06:09,827
Hey, Finn!

00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:11,796
Looks like the Smiths had
a guest last night.

00:06:11,796 --> 00:06:14,799
The towels are damp, and I found
a red hair in the shower drain.

00:06:14,799 --> 00:06:17,001
Hmm, that doesn't match either
of our victims.

00:06:17,001 --> 00:06:19,370
And there were three
toothbrushes around the sink.

00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:21,539
Uh, I found
a receipt for one.

00:06:21,539 --> 00:06:23,474
It's from the drugstore around
the corner--last night.

00:06:23,474 --> 00:06:25,076
So a guest they didn't plan on.

00:06:25,076 --> 00:06:27,144
There's more.
They also bought shampoo

00:06:27,144 --> 00:06:28,613
and a pair of scissors,

00:06:28,613 --> 00:06:31,148
which have since disappeared.

00:06:31,148 --> 00:06:33,718
Could be the murder weapon.

00:06:33,718 --> 00:06:36,587
So there was someone in here
before the killing started.
Yeah, who showered

00:06:36,587 --> 00:06:38,956
and-- I don't know-- judging
from the toothbrush,

00:06:38,956 --> 00:06:40,791
might've been planning
on staying the night.

00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:41,759
So what went wrong?

00:06:52,003 --> 00:06:53,838
I've been doing this
long enough that nothing

00:06:53,838 --> 00:06:55,473
shocks me,
but if a case could...

00:06:57,608 --> 00:07:00,912
Just the sheer savagery
involved.

00:07:00,912 --> 00:07:02,747
More than a hundred stab wounds
in each victim.

00:07:02,747 --> 00:07:05,383
Certainly beyond
what was necessary...

00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:07,985
if the goal was
to simply kill them.

00:07:07,985 --> 00:07:09,520
Can I see that?

00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,689
It's, uh, way beyond
what we sometimes see

00:07:11,689 --> 00:07:13,891
with crimes of passion
or extreme anger.

00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:14,959
This was madness.

00:07:17,361 --> 00:07:18,763
RUSSELL: Their names
really were Smith.

00:07:18,763 --> 00:07:20,364
ROBBINS:
Richard and Ann.

00:07:20,364 --> 00:07:22,667
According to family,
they were in from Flagstaff

00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:25,503
for an antique toy
and collectibles convention.

00:07:25,503 --> 00:07:27,605
That would explain
the dolls in the room.

00:07:27,605 --> 00:07:29,640
Sounds like they were
solid people.

00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:33,744
She volunteered, ran pet therapy
at an old folks home.

00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:35,146
He worked with the homeless.

00:07:36,814 --> 00:07:38,449
Squeaky clean.

00:07:38,449 --> 00:07:40,117
Course, that wouldn't be
the first time the...

00:07:40,117 --> 00:07:43,754
squeaky-clean have indulged
their dark side here in Vegas.

00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:45,456
They could've invited
somebody back to the room,

00:07:45,456 --> 00:07:46,891
spice up their life
a little bit.

00:07:48,659 --> 00:07:50,661
If so...

00:07:50,661 --> 00:07:53,898
certainly got more
than they bargained for.

00:07:53,898 --> 00:07:57,668
Hey. So, I... pulled the files

00:07:57,668 --> 00:07:59,837
for the other two
motel murder scenes.

00:07:59,837 --> 00:08:01,138
It's weird, don't you think?

00:08:01,138 --> 00:08:03,140
That a killer would fixate
on one room?

00:08:03,140 --> 00:08:04,775
What do you think
the significance is?

00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:05,876
Why does he feel
the need to kill there?

00:08:05,876 --> 00:08:07,445
Well, that's assuming

00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:09,747
that these are all the work
of one killer.

00:08:09,747 --> 00:08:11,615
It could be
that there's no connection.

00:08:11,615 --> 00:08:14,151
That you're looking for patterns
where there are none.

00:08:14,151 --> 00:08:16,954
So it's a coincidence that three
totally unrelated killers

00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:18,789
chose this one room?

00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:20,658
I'm just saying,
we don't know yet.

00:08:20,658 --> 00:08:22,893
All right,

00:08:22,893 --> 00:08:24,528
first one: Mark Bell.

00:08:24,528 --> 00:08:25,963
11 weeks ago,
he stayed

00:08:25,963 --> 00:08:29,567
in Room 114 after his girlfriend
kicked him out.

00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:31,635
Yeah, I remember.
I worked this case with Finn.

00:08:31,635 --> 00:08:34,005
The maid found him tied
to the bed,

00:08:34,005 --> 00:08:37,141
<i>severe lacerations to his legs.</i>
<i>They were nearly cut off.</i>

00:08:37,141 --> 00:08:38,909
<i>He bled to death.</i>

00:08:38,909 --> 00:08:40,678
<i>There was a bloody knife</i>
<i>found on the floor.</i>

00:08:40,678 --> 00:08:42,480
<i>Too smeared to yield</i>
<i>any viable prints.</i>

00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,582
<i>Detectives, at the time,</i>

00:08:44,582 --> 00:08:46,684
<i>thought the attack was related</i>
<i>to a drug debt.</i>
(screaming)

00:08:46,684 --> 00:08:49,153
<i>They thought the dealer</i>
<i>was sending a message.</i>

00:08:50,588 --> 00:08:53,457
Four weeks ago...

00:08:53,457 --> 00:08:54,992
second attack
in the room.

00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,894
Alex and Tina Garnez.

00:08:56,894 --> 00:08:59,096
Nick and I
handled this one.

00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:03,134
<i>Their house</i>
<i>had been foreclosed on.</i>

00:09:03,134 --> 00:09:05,503
<i>They were living in their car</i>
<i>for months.</i>

00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:08,406
<i>Mr. Garnez finally got a job.</i>

00:09:08,406 --> 00:09:11,142
<i>Moving to the motel was</i>
<i>supposed to be a step up.</i>

00:09:11,142 --> 00:09:14,612
<i>That night, he was sneaking</i>
<i>a cigarette in the bathroom</i>

00:09:14,612 --> 00:09:16,614
<i>while his wife slept.</i>

00:09:16,614 --> 00:09:18,516
<i>The killer started</i>
<i>with his wife...</i>

00:09:21,552 --> 00:09:24,155
<i>...clubbing her</i>
<i>while she was sleeping.</i>

00:09:24,155 --> 00:09:26,757
<i>Then he must've surprised</i>
<i>Mr. Garnez in the bathroom...</i>

00:09:26,757 --> 00:09:28,459
No!

00:09:28,459 --> 00:09:30,027
<i>Overpowered him.</i>

00:09:32,129 --> 00:09:34,365
He survived.

00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,534
He's still in the hospital
recovering.

00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,069
And then last night...

00:09:38,069 --> 00:09:39,070
the Smiths.

00:09:41,605 --> 00:09:43,874
(sighs)
Still think we're...

00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:46,143
dealing with random,
unrelated events?

00:09:46,143 --> 00:09:48,012
STOKES:
<i>All right, Finn,</i>

00:09:48,012 --> 00:09:49,980
I'll see you back at the lab.

00:09:54,085 --> 00:09:56,020
(helicopter hovering)

00:10:07,832 --> 00:10:10,701
Come on now. Open up.
I saw you in there.

00:10:11,769 --> 00:10:13,037
Hey.

00:10:13,037 --> 00:10:15,039
I was asleep last night.

00:10:15,039 --> 00:10:17,374
I was not involved.
I already told the cops.

00:10:17,374 --> 00:10:19,643
Oh, yeah, yeah. That's cool.
I'm not, uh...

00:10:19,643 --> 00:10:21,378
I'm not here to grill you.
(chuckles)

00:10:21,378 --> 00:10:24,682
Kind of looks like you like
to call this place home.

00:10:24,682 --> 00:10:26,817
I'm guessing you see everything
that goes on in here.

00:10:26,817 --> 00:10:28,652
You... didn't see
anything weird?

00:10:28,652 --> 00:10:30,888
Anybody suspicious
running around here lately?

00:10:30,888 --> 00:10:33,791
It's not my place to judge
another man in that way.

00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:35,659
Only God can judge.

00:10:35,659 --> 00:10:37,761
Right... well,
God would want you

00:10:37,761 --> 00:10:39,697
to help me catch a
killer, wouldn't he?

00:10:39,697 --> 00:10:41,098
I'm sorry.

00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:43,434
Now, sir, please, please,
hey, come on, now.

00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:46,804
A couple was violently
murdered last night.

00:10:46,804 --> 00:10:49,807
A woman a few weeks ago.
A young man before that.

00:10:49,807 --> 00:10:52,143
All in the same room,
all innocent victims.

00:10:52,143 --> 00:10:55,746
Innocent? There's no one
on this planet who's innocent.

00:10:57,047 --> 00:10:58,682
We're all sinners.

00:10:58,682 --> 00:11:00,985
Yeah, yeah, well, that-that

00:11:00,985 --> 00:11:02,553
doesn't really
help me do my job.

00:11:02,553 --> 00:11:04,421
They were called to God.

00:11:04,421 --> 00:11:05,756
That's God's plan.

00:11:07,091 --> 00:11:08,592
Your job is done.

00:11:08,592 --> 00:11:10,027
Yeah, I just...

00:11:13,497 --> 00:11:16,367
Might be my biggest
regret about this job--

00:11:16,367 --> 00:11:19,937
I know way too much
about hotel bedspreads.

00:11:19,937 --> 00:11:22,840
And hotel carpets.
Don't go barefoot.
So, we have

00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,742
three different bedspreads
from our...

00:11:24,742 --> 00:11:25,943
three different
crime scenes.

00:11:25,943 --> 00:11:27,111
I ran the DNA.

00:11:27,111 --> 00:11:28,779
The bedspread
on the left is

00:11:28,779 --> 00:11:30,981
from the very first
murder scene.
I'm guessing

00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:33,150
it lived in that room
for who knows how long.

00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:35,085
Long enough that I
was able to identify

00:11:35,085 --> 00:11:37,488
26 individual
DNA profiles.

00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,822
Whoa.
Yeah. The replacement

00:11:38,822 --> 00:11:41,158
bedspread there was
only in the room

00:11:41,158 --> 00:11:42,927
for seven weeks.
So fewer contributions.

00:11:42,927 --> 00:11:44,695
16 of them.

00:11:44,695 --> 00:11:47,698
And the third bedspread,
from last night's crime scene.

00:11:47,698 --> 00:11:49,567
Yielded only
nine contributors.

00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:51,869
But here's the thing:
One of them, a male,

00:11:51,869 --> 00:11:55,105
is common
to all three bedspreads.

00:11:55,105 --> 00:11:57,741
One person,
the same person was in the room

00:11:57,741 --> 00:11:59,109
before each of the murders?

00:12:00,611 --> 00:12:02,012
Have you run the samples
through CODIS?

00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,113
It's running
right now.

00:12:05,849 --> 00:12:08,152
Here we go.

00:12:08,152 --> 00:12:10,754
Randall Wicks, 22.
He must have

00:12:10,754 --> 00:12:12,523
just been added
to the system.

00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:15,559
There's why-- sexual battery
charge two weeks ago.

00:12:15,559 --> 00:12:16,994
Look where he was arrested.

00:12:18,662 --> 00:12:20,998
That same motel.
The same room!

00:12:20,998 --> 00:12:23,000
I'll call Brass,

00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,702
get out a broadcast.

00:12:30,941 --> 00:12:32,776
Oh, how the mighty have
fallen, huh, Randall?

00:12:32,776 --> 00:12:35,546
You used to be
the featured dancer
in the Tangiers

00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:36,847
All Male Review.

00:12:36,847 --> 00:12:38,582
How'd you let that
gig slip away?

00:12:38,582 --> 00:12:39,683
I don't know.

00:12:39,683 --> 00:12:41,719
I got bored, so I quit.

00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:44,755
Well, or maybe you
found something more
interesting to do, huh?

00:12:47,858 --> 00:12:50,127
Oh, hey, man, what the hell?
SANDERS: Three
separate murders

00:12:50,127 --> 00:12:52,496
in the same room at
the Sky View Motel.

00:12:52,496 --> 00:12:56,767
Your DNA was found in the room
after each of the crimes.

00:12:56,767 --> 00:13:00,571
What? Wait a minute--
Sky View Motel?

00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:02,506
Was that in room 114?

00:13:02,506 --> 00:13:04,642
I use that room,
frequently.

00:13:04,642 --> 00:13:05,776
For business.

00:13:05,776 --> 00:13:08,646
So... you're
a prostitute?

00:13:08,646 --> 00:13:11,448
Dude, I'm a stud,
letting frustrated housewives

00:13:11,448 --> 00:13:14,518
get a taste of something
they wouldn't even get
close to otherwise.

00:13:14,518 --> 00:13:17,454
Okay, stud, what
about the housewife
you beat up in room 114?

00:13:17,454 --> 00:13:19,156
The sexual
battery charge.

00:13:19,156 --> 00:13:21,425
Or was that just part of
the pony ride experience?

00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:23,394
That was self-defense.

00:13:23,394 --> 00:13:24,528
I'm serious.

00:13:24,528 --> 00:13:27,531
I was in fear for my life.

00:13:27,531 --> 00:13:28,899
Okay...

00:13:28,899 --> 00:13:30,901
I meet this woman there, right?

00:13:30,901 --> 00:13:33,003
Totally normal at first.

00:13:33,003 --> 00:13:35,072
Then we start
getting into it, and...

00:13:35,072 --> 00:13:37,541
I don't know,
she goes all crazy.

00:13:37,541 --> 00:13:39,543
Starts hallucinating
or something,

00:13:39,543 --> 00:13:40,878
screaming at the walls.

00:13:40,878 --> 00:13:43,147
Pure freak show.
SANDERS:
And why?

00:13:43,147 --> 00:13:45,382
What would make
her do that?

00:13:45,382 --> 00:13:47,551
Well, I ain't a doctor
or nothing, but...

00:13:47,551 --> 00:13:49,753
must be the sex
just blew her mind.

00:13:50,988 --> 00:13:52,823
Yeah, that must
have been it.

00:13:52,823 --> 00:13:55,492
(sighs): Well...
aside from being

00:13:55,492 --> 00:13:57,661
a complete tool,
what do you think?

00:13:57,661 --> 00:13:59,697
Well, he still
could be our killer.
Well, the problem is,

00:13:59,697 --> 00:14:01,565
all we have is DNA evidence,

00:14:01,565 --> 00:14:04,835
and we can't disprove his story
of how it got in that room.

00:14:04,835 --> 00:14:08,405
Well, we do have an eyewitness
who could possibly I.D. Randall.

00:14:08,405 --> 00:14:09,673
Alex Garnez, the husband

00:14:09,673 --> 00:14:11,575
who survived his wife
being bludgeoned

00:14:11,575 --> 00:14:13,911
four weeks ago.
He has massive head injuries.

00:14:13,911 --> 00:14:16,680
He's still in the hospital--
we don't even know what
condition he's in.

00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:17,981
Well, I talked to his doctor.

00:14:17,981 --> 00:14:20,384
She said he's struggling
psychologically.

00:14:20,384 --> 00:14:22,720
They have him on suicide watch
after one failed attempt,

00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,822
but... physically...

00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:27,558
she said he's strong
enough to talk to us.

00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:38,902
Mr. Garnez.

00:14:38,902 --> 00:14:40,637
Um...

00:14:40,637 --> 00:14:42,539
I'm CSI Brody,

00:14:42,539 --> 00:14:44,408
and this is

00:14:44,408 --> 00:14:45,743
CSI Sanders.

00:14:45,743 --> 00:14:48,545
I'm sorry,
but we need to talk to you

00:14:48,545 --> 00:14:51,048
about the night that
you and your wife were attacked.

00:14:53,117 --> 00:14:55,552
How much do you remember?

00:14:57,421 --> 00:15:00,057
(panting)

00:15:00,057 --> 00:15:01,725
I don't know.

00:15:01,725 --> 00:15:04,128
I... I...

00:15:04,128 --> 00:15:06,930
I remember her just lying there,

00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:10,134
just lying there.

00:15:10,134 --> 00:15:13,670
And all the...
blood around her...

00:15:17,608 --> 00:15:20,511
We were high school sweethearts.

00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:26,717
Did you see the person
who hurt you and your wife?

00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,754
Do you remember his face?

00:15:31,922 --> 00:15:35,125
(woman's faint, distorted cries)

00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:37,361
I can see him...

00:15:37,361 --> 00:15:40,097
standing over her,

00:15:40,097 --> 00:15:41,899
hitting her over...

00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,468
and over...

00:15:44,468 --> 00:15:46,804
and...

00:15:46,804 --> 00:15:48,372
and I'm powerless.

00:15:48,372 --> 00:15:51,575
I... I can't stop him.

00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:53,911
Like there's a wall
between us. I...

00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:57,648
Yet I can still hear the
sickening sound of...

00:15:57,648 --> 00:15:59,450
blow...

00:15:59,450 --> 00:16:01,051
after blow.

00:16:01,051 --> 00:16:03,020
Mr. Garnez...

00:16:03,020 --> 00:16:05,923
we want to... we want
to show you some photographs

00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,891
of some faces.

00:16:07,891 --> 00:16:10,494
We need you to tell us
if any one of these men

00:16:10,494 --> 00:16:13,564
looks like the man that
we've been talking about, okay?

00:16:18,068 --> 00:16:19,803
He's not there.

00:16:19,803 --> 00:16:21,472
Are you sure?

00:16:23,407 --> 00:16:24,942
None of these...

00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:28,078
is the man that
killed my Tina.

00:16:30,414 --> 00:16:33,684
Hodges, you texted me "911"?

00:16:33,684 --> 00:16:34,952
I did.

00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:36,787
What is the 911?

00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:39,022
Sorry. Your suspect.

00:16:39,022 --> 00:16:41,391
He ran from the motel
room barefoot, correct?

00:16:41,391 --> 00:16:42,426
Mm-hmm.

00:16:42,426 --> 00:16:43,727
Yet he left no shoes behind.

00:16:43,727 --> 00:16:45,362
He could have been
carrying his shoes.

00:16:45,362 --> 00:16:47,798
He was in too much
of a hurry to put them on.

00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:50,434
Mm, maybe. But there
was a bottle of shampoo

00:16:50,434 --> 00:16:51,902
that Nick found
in the bathroom.

00:16:51,902 --> 00:16:54,037
It contained
one percent permethrin,

00:16:54,037 --> 00:16:56,373
formulated to
combat head lice.

00:16:56,373 --> 00:16:57,841
Now, I've checked with Doc.

00:16:57,841 --> 00:17:00,444
Neither of the Smiths
were head lice sufferers.

00:17:00,444 --> 00:17:01,912
So the shampoo
was for the guest.

00:17:01,912 --> 00:17:04,448
Yes. Presumably the killer.

00:17:04,448 --> 00:17:06,116
Nick found residue on
the wall of the shower.

00:17:06,116 --> 00:17:09,553
I've tested it; it contained
<i>five</i> percent permethrin.

00:17:09,553 --> 00:17:11,555
Permethrin, for the head lice.
No.

00:17:11,555 --> 00:17:13,857
This is five percent,
in a body cream.

00:17:13,857 --> 00:17:16,960
It's prescription strength,
used to treat scabies.

00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,663
I don't want to seem
insensitive, but...

00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:21,365
shoeless, head lice,

00:17:21,365 --> 00:17:24,368
and scabies--that all
sounds like homeless to me.

00:17:24,368 --> 00:17:26,136
Richard Smith worked
with the homeless

00:17:26,136 --> 00:17:28,138
back in Flagstaff.

00:17:28,138 --> 00:17:31,141
He could have been doing
some sort of outreach,
wanted to help somebody,

00:17:31,141 --> 00:17:32,809
brought them in
off the street.

00:17:32,809 --> 00:17:34,511
I've already called around.

00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,013
There's a local shelter
called Street Saviors

00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:37,881
who had a scabies
outbreak last week,

00:17:37,881 --> 00:17:40,951
where they distributed this
very same prescription cream.

00:17:40,951 --> 00:17:43,587
Way to bury the lead, Hodges.
That's part
of my charm.

00:17:43,587 --> 00:17:45,022
It's all in the telling.

00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:46,456
FINLAY:
The regular.

00:17:46,456 --> 00:17:48,425
Yeah. Fruity.

00:17:48,425 --> 00:17:50,127
Okay, thanks so much.

00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:56,366
Hey. So I talked
to a couple
Hey.

00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:57,868
of the outreach
workers.

00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:00,938
They saw a guy earlier,
a guy named Rudy.

00:18:00,938 --> 00:18:02,472
He's a regular here.

00:18:02,472 --> 00:18:05,142
He was barefoot,
had bloodstained clothes.

00:18:05,142 --> 00:18:06,843
Sounds like our boy.

00:18:06,843 --> 00:18:08,445
FINLAY:
Yeah. According to the locals,

00:18:08,445 --> 00:18:09,880
he likes to hang out here,
under the bridge.

00:18:16,787 --> 00:18:17,988
Anybody seen Rudy?

00:18:17,988 --> 00:18:19,089
Huh?

00:18:20,123 --> 00:18:22,492
STOKES:
You seen Rudy?

00:18:22,492 --> 00:18:24,094
You know who Rudy is?

00:18:25,963 --> 00:18:27,664
Hey, where
does Rudy stay?

00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:34,972
Hey, old-timer.
Hey, man.

00:18:34,972 --> 00:18:37,074
You seen Rudy anywhere?

00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:54,725
Rudy!
(gasping)

00:18:54,725 --> 00:18:56,360
What's wrong?

00:18:57,461 --> 00:18:59,463
What have you
been doing, man?

00:19:00,530 --> 00:19:02,366
(panting)
Huh?

00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:07,671
Rudy, you're gonna have
to come with us.

00:19:07,671 --> 00:19:09,740
Rudy, it says here
in my files

00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:12,075
that you spent some time
in the state hospital.

00:19:12,075 --> 00:19:13,543
Had a few psych holds?

00:19:13,543 --> 00:19:16,680
Yeah, I have some problems.

00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,415
What did the doctors
diagnose you with?

00:19:19,516 --> 00:19:22,819
Schizophrenia, bipolar disorder,

00:19:22,819 --> 00:19:24,888
generalized anxiety,

00:19:24,888 --> 00:19:26,823
paranoia...
BRASS:
Well, that's okay.

00:19:26,823 --> 00:19:28,892
We get the idea.

00:19:28,892 --> 00:19:31,528
Do you recognize these two?
Richard and Ann?

00:19:31,528 --> 00:19:33,563
They're angels.

00:19:33,563 --> 00:19:36,833
What do you mean?
They rescued me.

00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:39,069
How?
I was on the
street, out front

00:19:39,069 --> 00:19:41,838
of a drugstore on Cramer.
Oh, that's

00:19:41,838 --> 00:19:44,374
right near
the Sky View Motel.
I go there sometimes

00:19:44,374 --> 00:19:47,577
to ask for change,
you know, and-and I...

00:19:47,577 --> 00:19:48,979
These guys,

00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,847
they jumped me and-and...

00:19:50,847 --> 00:19:52,649
and they beat me,

00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:55,986
and they took my change
and they took my shoes.

00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,754
And-and it probably
would have been worse,

00:19:57,754 --> 00:19:59,523
except that Richard and Ann
came along

00:19:59,523 --> 00:20:00,724
out of nowhere and...

00:20:00,724 --> 00:20:03,660
and chased them away.

00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:04,795
Rudy, what happened next?

00:20:07,764 --> 00:20:10,534
I told you, they're angels.

00:20:10,534 --> 00:20:12,636
They-they-they...

00:20:12,636 --> 00:20:14,104
they asked me if
I wanted to stay

00:20:14,104 --> 00:20:16,873
in their room with them,
and they got me a toothbrush

00:20:16,873 --> 00:20:19,443
and stuff, and they let me
get a shower

00:20:19,443 --> 00:20:21,078
and get all cleaned up.

00:20:21,078 --> 00:20:22,679
Did something happen
after the shower?

00:20:24,748 --> 00:20:26,116
Something happened, didn't it?

00:20:28,585 --> 00:20:29,753
(mutters): I don't know.

00:20:29,753 --> 00:20:31,488
I don't remember.

00:20:31,488 --> 00:20:33,557
Come on, Rudy, think.

00:20:33,557 --> 00:20:36,393
Think real hard.
(shuddering breath)

00:20:36,393 --> 00:20:37,360
(distorted shout):
No! No!

00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:44,701
There were these dolls...

00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:46,737
<i>a-and there were</i>
<i>a whole bunch of them,</i>

00:20:46,737 --> 00:20:50,006
<i>and they started talking to me</i>
<i>and they were looking at me.</i>

00:20:50,006 --> 00:20:51,108
(distorted screaming,
eerie voices speaking)

00:20:53,110 --> 00:20:55,579
What were they saying, Rudy?
What did they say?

00:20:55,579 --> 00:20:59,649
Did the dolls
tell you to do this?

00:20:59,649 --> 00:21:01,518
(gasps, screams)

00:21:01,518 --> 00:21:02,586
I...

00:21:05,388 --> 00:21:08,125
I did that, didn't I?
I did that with the scissors.

00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:09,760
I hurt them.

00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,128
(shrieking)

00:21:11,128 --> 00:21:12,562
(eerie, distorted,
high-pitched laughter)

00:21:12,562 --> 00:21:13,597
(shriek echoing)

00:21:13,597 --> 00:21:15,632
What about these people?

00:21:15,632 --> 00:21:17,434
(Rudy gasping repeatedly)

00:21:19,369 --> 00:21:20,570
Did you hurt them, too?

00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:25,809
I don't know.

00:21:25,809 --> 00:21:28,478
FINLAY: <i>You know, sometimes</i>
<i>I think we forget</i>

00:21:28,478 --> 00:21:30,914
what delicate,
complex machines we are.

00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:34,651
You know, all it takes are a few
short-circuiting synapses,

00:21:34,651 --> 00:21:37,120
or a breakdown
in myelination,

00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:38,922
and everything gets thrown
out of whack.

00:21:38,922 --> 00:21:41,691
Jules, you just
captured a killer.

00:21:41,691 --> 00:21:44,694
I know.
Then why do I feel so bad?

00:21:44,694 --> 00:21:46,062
Because he seems like
a nice guy

00:21:46,062 --> 00:21:48,031
who got dealt a lousy hand
in life.

00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:53,003
So we have him for killing
the Smiths, right?

00:21:53,003 --> 00:21:54,871
What about the other
two attacks?

00:21:54,871 --> 00:21:57,941
Well, I could go over all the
evidence and make a case.

00:21:57,941 --> 00:21:59,910
He's obviously
our prime suspect.

00:21:59,910 --> 00:22:04,548
He frequented the area,
and he's obviously unstable.

00:22:07,384 --> 00:22:08,685
Good work.

00:22:08,685 --> 00:22:10,821
You put some long hours
in on this.

00:22:10,821 --> 00:22:12,088
Why-why don't you go home,

00:22:12,088 --> 00:22:14,057
get yourself some rest.

00:22:27,671 --> 00:22:31,074
(TV playing indistinctly
in distance)

00:22:31,074 --> 00:22:33,643
(yelling, panting)

00:22:33,643 --> 00:22:35,712
Take it, take it easy!

00:22:35,712 --> 00:22:37,914
One plus one is two.
One for me and one for you.

00:22:37,914 --> 00:22:40,917
Two plus two is four. (panting)

00:22:40,917 --> 00:22:43,386
<i>That's a couple more.</i>
<i>Three plus three is six.</i>

00:22:43,386 --> 00:22:44,588
<i>Straight and crooked sticks!</i>

00:22:44,588 --> 00:22:45,589
Get away!

00:22:45,589 --> 00:22:48,992
(siren wailing)

00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:50,460
(muttering)

00:22:50,460 --> 00:22:51,461
One plus one is two.

00:22:51,461 --> 00:22:52,996
One for me and one for you.

00:22:52,996 --> 00:22:54,431
Two plus two is four,
and that's a couple more.

00:22:54,431 --> 00:22:55,899
(gasping)

00:22:55,899 --> 00:22:57,701
One plus one is two.
One for me and one for you.

00:22:57,701 --> 00:22:59,035
Two plus two is four.
That's a couple more.

00:22:59,035 --> 00:23:00,470
Three plus
three is six.
Ma'am.

00:23:00,470 --> 00:23:01,771
Straight and crooked sticks.

00:23:01,771 --> 00:23:03,006
You need to drop
that bottle, do you hear me?

00:23:03,006 --> 00:23:04,574
(whimpering)

00:23:04,574 --> 00:23:05,976
Four plus four is eight.
Seagulls on the gate!

00:23:05,976 --> 00:23:07,744
Five plus five is ten.
Hey!

00:23:07,744 --> 00:23:09,112
Do you hear
what I'm saying?!

00:23:09,112 --> 00:23:12,449
Drop the bottle!

00:23:12,449 --> 00:23:13,984
Ricky doesn't follow directions!

00:23:13,984 --> 00:23:17,020
He never follows directions!

00:23:18,088 --> 00:23:19,122
(yells)

00:23:19,122 --> 00:23:21,091
(Tazer clicking)

00:23:23,126 --> 00:23:24,461
Thanks, man.

00:23:24,461 --> 00:23:26,897
Seriously, thanks.

00:23:26,897 --> 00:23:28,531
Thanks.
All right.

00:23:28,531 --> 00:23:29,699
(gasps)

00:23:29,699 --> 00:23:31,001
Hey!

00:23:31,001 --> 00:23:32,569
Was she staying here?
In the motel?

00:23:32,569 --> 00:23:34,638
Uh, yeah, just
since tonight.

00:23:35,472 --> 00:23:36,439
What room?

00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:45,982
(door creaking)

00:23:48,485 --> 00:23:50,153
It's happened again.

00:23:59,496 --> 00:24:01,431
(indistinct radio communication,
siren whoops in distance)

00:24:20,650 --> 00:24:22,719
How the hell can this be?

00:24:22,719 --> 00:24:24,154
I thought we had our killer.

00:24:24,154 --> 00:24:26,523
Did we mess up, Jules?

00:24:26,523 --> 00:24:28,091
Did we make a mistake
with our-our homeless guy?

00:24:28,091 --> 00:24:30,794
No, Rudy's guilty,
maybe not of all three,

00:24:30,794 --> 00:24:32,796
but he definitely
killed the Smiths.

00:24:32,796 --> 00:24:33,930
Then how do we explain this?

00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:35,065
I don't know.

00:24:35,065 --> 00:24:37,133
It has to be... unrelated.

00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:38,702
Unrelated?

00:24:38,702 --> 00:24:40,470
Four murders in the same room

00:24:40,470 --> 00:24:42,005
over a three-month period.

00:24:42,005 --> 00:24:43,807
That's got to be connected,
don't you think?

00:24:43,807 --> 00:24:44,975
(garbled radio transmission)

00:24:46,743 --> 00:24:49,946
All right, I'm sorry. Look,

00:24:49,946 --> 00:24:51,414
all right, who are
our players tonight?

00:24:51,414 --> 00:24:53,049
Who are we talking about here?

00:24:53,049 --> 00:24:55,552
Suspect is a woman,

00:24:55,552 --> 00:24:57,921
28-year-old
high school math teacher.

00:24:57,921 --> 00:25:00,824
Victim was one of her students.

00:25:00,824 --> 00:25:03,927
Together in a sleazy,
$39-a-night motel room.

00:25:03,927 --> 00:25:08,932
With lingerie, condoms,
sex toys and alcohol.

00:25:08,932 --> 00:25:10,500
Wonder what
was going on here, right?

00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:12,035
Yeah, according

00:25:12,035 --> 00:25:13,436
to the high school Web site,

00:25:13,436 --> 00:25:14,904
she was just named
Teacher of the Year.

00:25:14,904 --> 00:25:16,106
I'll bet she was.

00:25:16,106 --> 00:25:17,474
Hey.
Hey.

00:25:17,474 --> 00:25:18,842
So, this may

00:25:18,842 --> 00:25:20,577
sound crazy,
but I'm thinking

00:25:20,577 --> 00:25:22,545
that this isn't
what it looks like.

00:25:22,545 --> 00:25:23,780
I don't believe
that the teacher

00:25:23,780 --> 00:25:25,148
was sleeping with her student.

00:25:25,148 --> 00:25:26,983
Yeah, you're right,
that sounds crazy.

00:25:26,983 --> 00:25:28,718
Well, listen to this voice mail

00:25:28,718 --> 00:25:30,120
I found on her phone.

00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:31,154
YOUNG MAN:
Ms. Stone, it's Matthew.

00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:32,722
I don't know what to do,

00:25:32,722 --> 00:25:35,392
but my parents have been
drinking and fighting,

00:25:35,392 --> 00:25:37,827
and I can't go home;

00:25:37,827 --> 00:25:40,563
I'm at a motel.

00:25:40,563 --> 00:25:41,698
But I'm scared.

00:25:41,698 --> 00:25:43,600
I don't know who else to call.

00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,102
I'm sorry, but you have
to help, please.

00:25:46,102 --> 00:25:49,139
BRASS: Ms. Stone, we are
trying to make sense

00:25:49,139 --> 00:25:52,876
out of what happened
in that room.

00:25:52,876 --> 00:25:54,611
